title: Victorian boy, three, killed in quad bike accident
text:
A three-year-old boy has been killed in a freak quad bike accident in rural east Victoria on Sunday.

The toddler was at a property in Deddick Valley when he suffered severe injuries as a result of the tragic accident.

Emergency services were called to the property on the New South Wales-Victorian border at 10.30am on Sunday.

Attempts to revive the boy by paramedics were unsuccessful.

A report will be prepared for the coroner as the circumstances surrounding the death are investigated.
